{{Stub|Not much information here! Please expand and proofread in reference to the [[VRCWiki:Manual_of_Style|Manual of Style]].}}'''Music culture''', and '''dance culture''' have a prominent scene in VRChat. The music scene includes community-created, and VRChat-partnered music events, and groups taking place in real time, inside of [[Worlds|worlds]] designed as nightclubs or venues, to mimic the feeling of being at a similar venue in real life.

In these events, VRChat users designate themselves as [[Wikipedia:Disc_jockey|disc jockeys]] (DJs), who can control physical DJ hardware, and simultaneously broadcast their DJ mixes into the world via [[Open Sound Control|Open Sound Control.]] often using livestreaming services like [[Trusted URLs|Twitch, or VRCDN]], in conjunction with a [[Video players|video player]]. In contrast, attendees come to listen to the music, and dance to it, sometimes with [[Full-Body Tracking|full-body tracking]] (FBT) peripherals, to move their legs and other limbs.

Some music events can also include live singing, karaoke, and group dancing.

